==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Midden
<hw>Mid"den</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Also
<asp>midding</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[Cf. Dan. <ets>m⟦oum⟧gdynge</ets>, E.
<ets>muck</ets>, and <ets>dung</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A dunghill.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An accumulation of refuse about a dwelling place;
especially, an accumulation of shells or of cinders, bones, and other
refuse on the supposed site of the dwelling places of prehistoric
tribes, -- as on the shores of the Baltic Sea and in many other places.
See <er>Kitchen middens</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Midden crow</ent>⟦br⟧
